    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Type&nbsp;</strong>disease (injury or ingested); <strong>Save&nbsp;</strong>Fortitude DC 18;</p>\n<p><strong>Onset&nbsp;</strong><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListDiseases_ctl00_LabelName\">1 day</span>;&nbsp;<strong>Frequency&nbsp;</strong>1/day</p>\n<p><strong>Effect&nbsp;</strong>1d3 Con damage and 1d6 Wis damage, and victim is&nbsp;<a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; background-image: none; background-color: initial; padding: 0px; font-family: OlsenTF; font-size: 13.3333px; color: #ff6400; margin: 0px; border: none;\" draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf1.conditions\" data-id=\"nku8mgRBNt0iXqzB\"><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; text-decoration-line: underline;\">fatigued</span></a><a draggable=\"false\" data-pack=\"pf1.conditions\" data-id=\"nku8mgRBNt0iXqzB\">&nbsp;</a>if it takes any ability damage from the disease; certain creatures slain by demonplague rise as plagued beasts</p>\n<p><strong>Cure&nbsp;</strong>3 consecutive saves</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Of the afflictions wreaked upon Sarkoris by the Worldwound and Deskari&rsquo;s host, the demonplague is perhaps the most insidious. This vile sickness spreads through water, affecting plant and animal life alike. In higher creatures, the demonplague causes madness and then death, but in animals and other unintelligent beasts, it continues beyond death, animating them as undead horrors called plagued beasts. The plague also twists and corrupts plant life&mdash; most of the hazardous plants detailed below are the results of normal plants becoming corrupted by the demonplague.</p>",
